# PE Image Storage — Cloudinary Migration Threshold

Proposal Engine custom-section images are currently stored as **base64 in `pe_proposals` (Neon DB TOAST)**.
This is intentional and acceptable today. CRM project documents already use Cloudinary correctly.

## Current state (May 2026)
- 32 proposals · ~2 MB TOAST · ~64 KB per proposal
- No action needed until threshold below is reached

## Trigger thresholds
| `pe_proposals` TOAST size | Action |
|---|---|
| < 10 MB | Monitor only |
| 10–20 MB | Begin Cloudinary migration sprint for PE image uploads |
| > 20 MB | Stop adding image features in PE until migrated |

## Monitoring query (run in Neon SQL Editor)
```sql
SELECT pg_size_pretty(pg_relation_size(t.oid)) AS pe_proposals_blob_size
FROM pg_class c
JOIN pg_class t ON c.reltoastrelid = t.oid
WHERE c.relname = 'pe_proposals';
```

## When migration is triggered, change these two things only
1. `proposal-engine/frontend/src/components/CustomSectionsBeforeBoq.tsx`
   — replace `compressImageFileToDataUrl()` with upload-to-Cloudinary → insert returned URL
2. Add `POST /api/proposal-engine/upload-image` route using existing Cloudinary credentials
   (same `CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME/API_KEY/API_SECRET` already in Render — no new account needed)

Existing base64 images in old proposals remain valid — no backfill required at migration time.

## Reminder dates
- Aug 2026 — run monitoring query
- Nov 2026 — run again; schedule sprint if > 10 MB
- Feb 2027 — treat as P1 if > 15 MB and not yet done

Full plan: `docs/pe-image-storage-migration-plan.md`
